[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] These properties are defined on `String.prototype` and shared by all `String` instances.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] The constructor function that created the instance object.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] For `String` instances, the initial value is the `String` constructor.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] These properties are own properties of each `String` instance.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Returns the character (exactly one UTF-16 code unit) at the specified `index`.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Accepts negative integers, which count back from the last string character.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Returns a number that is the UTF-16 code unit value at the given `index`.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Returns a nonnegative integer Number that is the code point value of the UTF-16 encoded code point starting at the specified `pos`.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Combines the text of two (or more) strings and returns a new string.
