[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Returns a boolean indicating whether this string contains any lone surrogates.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Returns the index within this string of the last occurrence of `searchValue`, or `-1` if not found.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Returns a number indicating whether the reference string `compareString` comes before, after, or is equivalent to the given string in sort order.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Used to match regular expression `regexp` against a string.
[src:chalk-terminal/global-objects-string] Returns an iterator of all `regexp`'s matches.
